DataElement.preferredName: Hematology Oxygen Saturation Laboratory Lab Percentage ULN Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The numeric laboratory value representing the upper level of the normal range of values of the hematology oxygen saturation.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the determination of oxygen-hemoglobin saturation of blood either by withdrawing a sample and passing it through a classical photoelectric oximeter or by electrodes attached to some translucent part of the body like finger, earlobe, or skin fold. It includes non-invasive oxygen monitoring by pulse oximetry.
